        "text": "Yes. An active dispute involving the lot or the body corporate scheme is a material fact that sellers must disclose to buyers before the contract is entered into. This includes disputes between lot owners, disputes between a lot owner and the body corporate or committee, and any active proceedings before the Commissioner for Body Corporate and Community Management or QCAT. Buyers who discover an undisclosed active dispute through a body corporate records search have grounds to seek contract termination or price reduction."
