        "text": "The Commissioner for Body Corporate and Community Management (BCCM) is the first port of call for most body corporate disputes in Queensland. Disputes are referred to the BCCM for conciliation or adjudication. If conciliation fails and the dispute is not resolved by the BCCM adjudicator, or if the parties seek a different forum, the matter can be escalated to QCAT (Queensland Civil and Administrative Tribunal). QCAT has broader powers and its orders are more readily enforced, but proceedings at QCAT are more formal and expensive than BCCM conciliation."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a building defect dispute and how does it affect a Queensland unit sale?",
